{
  "stem": "6052.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But later, when he came, he continued in his profession or in his trade in Leipzig.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My mother helped him at that time, and the conditions were quite favorable for Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The fact is that in Leipzig lived at that time about 20,000 Jews, and apparently, the possibilities to live in a better lifestyle than over where they came from.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Most of the Jews who came from Poland-- this shows that the prosperity was something which kept them there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were, of course, people who lived a longer time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The fact is that Jews lived in Europe for, what, for about 2,000 years?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I looked up the historical books, I see that Jews came to Leipzig, or they are mentioned in the records of Leipzig, as of the year 1352.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in the year 1848, the Jews were given equal rights and these equal rights were, of course, trampled on the minute Hitler came to power.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What was your particular family life like?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Did you have sisters, brothers?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had three-- one brother who survived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had also three wonderful sisters who were murdered together with my mother when they were deported from Leipzig to Riga.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the continuation of my story, I will tell you how-- what-- how I came about to know about the deportation and where from.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the first calamity occurred with the murder of my father in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And see, life in Leipzig, just not to jump ahead too much, was very good to me, I felt, as a child who went there to school and finished.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was among those who could finish eight years of schooling in Leipzig because at the end of the eight year, the Kristallnacht showed us that it could not be any continuation.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
